prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "school-grid-paper-cutout-poster" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: warm cream classroom grid paper background, straight-on copy-stand view, one oversized torn-paper collage object centered slightly right of the hand-written text block, generous empty grid space, and a narrow pale bottom margin.
- Typography: one compact vertical column or two slim vertical columns of loose hand-drawn notebook characters on the upper-left side, dark graphite or faded ink, uneven and human, never clean digital type.
- Color: mostly yellowed beige paper with muted blue-green grid lines, cream torn-paper layers, one saturated cut-paper accent color, and tiny dark handwritten marks.
- Texture and lighting: real paper grain, deckled torn fibers, slight scan softness, low contrast vintage print finish, soft diffuse overhead light, and shallow physical shadows under lifted paper edges.
- Graphic elements: ruled grid structure, torn paper silhouette, optional tiny generic seal-like mark, and a small bottom caption strip; keep all marks generic.

Avoid: no ice cream, no soft-serve shape, no cone silhouette, no fast-food branding, no recognizable logo, no original Chinese headline, no source watermark or signature, no dense scene, no glossy product render, no 3D object, no vector poster, no QR code.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
